PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,FRobbins has claimed that when he took
OL,7,Fover the helm of the foreign office in
OL,8,FJanuary last year, Mandelson had
OL,9,Falready gone through the Cabinet
OL,10,FOffice's "due diligence" process, the
OL,11,FKing and the US had given him
OL,12,Fapproval, and he was already being
OL,13,Fgranted access to "highly classified
OL,14,Fbriefings" on a case-by-case basis `
OL,15,Fwithout his security clearance being
OL,16,Fconfirmed.
OL,18,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,19,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,20,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,21,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,FCriticising Starmer's judgement in
OL,7,Fappointing Mandelson, Tory leader Kemi
OL,8,FBadenoch questioned why Starmer had
OL,9,Fignored the advice of then Cabinet
OL,10,FSecretary Simon Case to carry out
OL,11,Fvetting prior to announcing
OL,12,FMandelson's appointment.
OL,14,FResponding, the PM insisted "due
OL,15,Fprocess" had been followed and that it
OL,16,Fwas right to sack Robbins.
OL,18,FEarlier on Wednesday, Cabinet minister
OL,19,FPat McFadden repeatedly declined to
OL,20,Fsay he believed Robbins' sacking was
OL,21,Ffair.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,FSpeaking on Times Radio, Mr McFadden
OL,7,Fsaid he thought "very highly" of
OL,8,FRobbins but, "I think if the Prime
OL,9,FMinister's made the judgment that he's
OL,10,Fnot got confidence in the head of the
OL,11,Fforeign office, the head of the
OL,12,Fforeign service, then it's difficult
OL,13,Fto continue".
OL,15,FAsked again if it was fair, Mr
OL,16,FMcFadden said: "Look, it's the Prime
OL,17,FMinister's judgment."
OL,19,FAsked the same question again, Mr
OL,20,FMcFadden said: "As a Cabinet member, I
OL,21,Fsupport the prime minister's decisions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,F"He took the decision he couldn't
OL,7,Fcontinue with Olly Robbins in post
OL,8,Fbecause he viewed the material that
OL,9,Fhad been withheld from him, not shared
OL,10,Fwith him, as really important in
OL,11,Fmaking this decision."
OL,13,FFormer civil service chief Lord
OL,14,FSedwill said Sir Robbins should be
OL,15,Freinstated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,F"Olly Robbins acted with the calm
OL,7,Fintegrity and intelligence that have
OL,8,Fdefined his public service," he said.
OL,9,F"His job was to judge whether
OL,10,FMandelson's risks could be mitigated,
OL,11,Fnot tell the PM what he already knew.
OL,13,F"Starmer should retract his
OL,14,Faccusations and reinstate him."
OL,16,FDave Penman, general secretary of the
OL,17,FFDA union, which represents senior
OL,18,Fcivil servants, said the sacking had
OL,19,Fsent a "chill" through Whitehall.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@\O]qD@AOUuD@AOUvD@_O]{D@HOU{D@
OL,26,ANO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,F"Government only works when there is
OL,7,Ftrust between ministers and civil
OL,8,Fservants," he warned.
OL,10,FBoth Tory leader Kemi Badenoch, and
OL,11,Fthe SNP have called for Labour to hold
OL,12,Fa vote of no confidence in Starmer,
OL,13,Fwhilst Reform, the Lib Dems, and the
OL,14,FGreens have all called for his
OL,15,Fresignation.
OL,17,FThe prime minister was also grilled
OL,18,Fover Robbin's claim on Tuesday that
OL,19,FDowning Street had sought a diplomatic
OL,20,Fposition for former communications
OL,21,Fchief Matthew Doyle.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
