PN,30612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,FLord Doyle had the Labour whip
OL,7,Fwithdrawn earlier this year after it
OL,8,Femerged he had campaigned on behalf of
OL,9,Fa friend who had been charged with
OL,10,Fpossessing indecent images of children.
OL,12,FThe peer apologised for backing then
OL,13,Fcouncillor Sean Morton before the case
OL,14,Fagainst him had concluded, saying he
OL,15,Fbelieved the paedophile's assertions
OL,16,Fof innocence before Morton later
OL,17,Fadmitted the offending.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776931533
OL,3,CPM claims civil servant's evidence
OL,4,C'put to bed' allegations against him
OL,6,FAsked at PMQs whether he could deny
OL,7,Fthat Downing Street had sought this,
OL,8,FStarmer said: "When people leave roles
OL,9,Fin any organisation, there are often
OL,10,Fconversations about other roles they
OL,11,Fwant to apply for, but nothing came of
OL,12,Fthis."
OL,14,FThe PM also refused to directly
OL,15,Faddress a question by Lib Dem leader
OL,16,FSir Ed Davey, who asked if he had been
OL,17,Faware his office was lobbying the
OL,18,FForeign Office for a role for Doyle.
OL,26,@pD@OOUtD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
